ATHX A preliminary analysis of the biomarkers reveals that similar to results from the Companys MultiStem MASTERS1 study for acute ischemic stroke there was an overall reduction in proinammatory cytokines in the MultiStem treatment group compared to placebo group Specically certain acute inammatory cytokines were lower in the ARDS patients that received MultiStem The same inammatory cytokines were also downregulated in the stroke patients that were in the MultiStem treatment group in the MASTERS1 study suggesting that MultiStem may work in similar way for both ARDS and stroke
